PointEvent.label: Point event
PointEvent.description: An event emanating from or targeting a Point; e.g., an individual Observation from a Sensor point, or an Actuation sent to a Command point. In other terms, the Points indicate the capability of some Space or Equipment to emit or accept data, while this class represents those actual data messages. Note that in most non-trivially sized systems, these events are not stored in the knowledge graph itself, but are rather forwarded to some C&C system or time series database.

Event.label: Event
Event.description: A temporally indexed entity, e.g., an observation, a lease, a construction project, etc. Can be instantaneous (timestamp property assigned) or have temporal extent (start and end properties assigned). Subclasses may define specific behaviour and requirements, e.g., on spatial indexing, agent participation, etc.

Zone.label: Zone
Zone.description: A sub-zone within or outside of a building defined to support some technology and/or use, e.g., an HVAC zone, a parking space, a security zone, etc.

Architecture.label: Architecture
Architecture.description: A designed/landscaped (or potentially designed/landscaped) part of the physical world that has a 3D spatial extent. E.g., a building site, a building, levels within the building, rooms, etc.

Space.label: Space
Space.description: A contiguous part of the physical world that contains or can contain sub-spaces. E.g., a Region can contain many Sites, which in turn can contain many Buildings.

Asset.label: Asset
Asset.description: Something which is placed inside of a building, but is not an integral part of that building's structure; e.g., furniture, equipment, systems, etc.

Room.label: Room
Room.description: Base class for all more specific room types.

Agent.label: Agent
Agent.description: The human, group, or machine that consumes or acts upon an object or data. This higher-level grouping allows properties that are shared among its subclasses (Person, Organization, ....) to be anchored in one joint place, on the Agent class.

Collection.label: Collection
Collection.description: An administrative grouping of entities that are adressed and treated as a unit for some purpose. These entities may have some spatial arrangement (e.g., an apartment is typically contiguous) but that is not a requirement (see, e.g., a distributed campus consisting of spatially disjoint plots or buildings). Inclusion in a Collection is determined by the 'includes' field on a specific subclass.

ArchitectureArea.label: Architecture area
ArchitectureArea.description: Describes business-relevant area measurements typically associated with architected spaces. As the exact requirements on these measurements will vary from case to case or jurisdiction to jurisdiction, subclassing and specializing this definition is encouraged.

ArchitectureCapacity.label: Architecture capacity
ArchitectureCapacity.description: Describes business-relevant capacity measurements typically associated with architected spaces. As the exact requirements on these measurements will vary from case to case or jurisdiction to jurisdiction, subclassing and specializing this definition is encouraged.

Atrium.label: Atrium
Atrium.description: a large open-air or skylight covered space surrounded by a building.

ICTEquipment.label: ICT Equipment
ICTEquipment.description: Equipment and devices that are part of a building's ICT infrastructure.

Equipment.label: Equipment
Equipment.description: devices that serve all or part of the building and may include electric power, lighting, transportation, or service water heating, including, but not limited to, furnaces, boilers, air conditioners, heat pumps, chillers, water heaters, lamps, luminaires, ballasts, elevators, escalators, or other devices or installations.

Auditorium.label: Auditorium
Auditorium.description: A space for performances or larger gatherings

BuildingElement.label: Building element
BuildingElement.description: A part that constitutes a piece of a building's structural makeup. E.g., Facade, Wall, Slab, Roof, etc.

Level.label: Level
Level.description: The level of a building, a.k.a. storey, floor, etc.

Furniture.label: Furniture
Furniture.description: Movable objects intended to support various human activities such as seating, eating and sleeping

BooleanValueObservation.label: Boolean value observation
BooleanValueObservation.description: Generic xsd:boolean value observation that is not specific to any particular QUDT quantitykind or unit.

Campus.label: Campus
Campus.description: A campus represents a collection of location entities. The constituent locations may have differing legal ownership and utilization purposes, but they are generally perceived as a coherent unit or sub-region within a city or other region. E.g., a university campus, a hospital campus, a corporate campus, etc.

Organization.label: Organization
Organization.description: An organization of any sort (e.g., a business, association, project, consortium, tribe, etc.)

DoubleValueObservation.label: Double value observation
DoubleValueObservation.description: Generic xsd:double value observation that is not specific to any particular QUDT quantitykind or unit.

Entrance.label: Entrance
Entrance.description: The location and space of a building where people enter and exit the building

Georeference.label: Georeference
Georeference.description: A georeference creates a relationship between a local coordinate system into a geographic coordinate system.

Geotransform.label: Geotransform
Geotransform.description: A transform following GDAL's Affine Transform that transforms a local coordinate into a WGS84 coordinate. Created from Ground Control Points (GCP) using GDAL's GCPsToGeotransform method.

Hallway.label: Hallway
Hallway.description: A common space, used to connect other parts of a building

IntegerValueObservation.label: Integer value observation
IntegerValueObservation.description: Generic xsd:int value observation that is not specific to any particular QUDT quantitykind or unit.

Laboratory.label: Laboratory
Laboratory.description: facility acceptable to the local, national, or international recognized authority having jurisdiction and which provides uniform testing and examination procedures and standards for meeting design, manufacturing, and factory testing requirements.

LeaseContract.label: Lease contract
LeaseContract.description: Formal document that identifies the Tenant and the leased asset or property; states lease term and fee (rent), and detailed terms and conditions of the lease agreement.

Library.label: Library
Library.description: A place for the storage and/or consumption of physical media, e.g. books, periodicals, and DVDs/CDs

OccupancyZone.label: Occupancy zone
OccupancyZone.description: Occupancy Zone is a spatial area where devices are monitoring or reporting on the concept of Occupancy (motion sensors, people counters, cameras, etc.)

Office.label: Office
Office.description: A class of rooms dedicated for work or study

Person.label: Person
Person.description: A natural person (i.e., an individual human being).

Portfolio.label: Portfolio
Portfolio.description: A portfolio is a grouping of buildings, sites, apartments, campuses, etc. that share some business-relevant commonality, e.g., are managed by the same company, are rented out to the same tenant, share utilization or legal definition (industrial vs commercial), etc.

Premises.label: Premises
Premises.description: A premises is an administrative grouping of spaces that are used for some commercial or industrial purpose by a real estate holder or tenant. E.g, a suite of offices, a shop, or an industrial workshop.

RealEstate.label: Real Estate
RealEstate.description: The legal/administrative representation of some lands and/or buildings. I.e., "Fastighet" (Swedish), "Ejendom" (Denmark), etc.

Reception.label: Reception
Reception.description: A space, usually in a lobby, where visitors to a building or space can go to after arriving at a building and inform building staff that they have arrived

Region.label: Region
Region.description: An administrative geospatial unit larger than the individual real estate. For instance, "Lombary", "North America", "The Back Bay", "Elnätsområde Syd", etc.

Site.label: Site
Site.description: A piece of land upon which zero or more buildings may be situated.

Workshop.label: Workshop
Workshop.description: A space used to house equipment that can be used to repair or fabricate things

Ablutions_Room.label: Ablutions Room
Ablutions_Room.description: A room for performing cleansing rituals before prayer

Absolute_Humidity_Sensor.label: Absolute Humidity Sensor
Absolute_Humidity_Sensor.description: Measures the present state of absolute humidity

Humidity_Sensor.label: Humidity Sensor
Humidity_Sensor.description: Measures the concentration of water vapor in air

Sensor.label: Sensor
Sensor.description: A Sensor is an input point that represents the value of a device or instrument designed to detect and measure a variable (ASHRAE Dictionary).

Absorption_Chiller.label: Absorption Chiller
Absorption_Chiller.description: A chiller that utilizes a thermal or/and chemical process to produce the refrigeration effect necessary to provide chilled water. There is no mechanical compression of the refrigerant taking place within the machine, as occurs within more traditional vapor compression type chillers.

Chiller.label: Chiller
Chiller.description: Refrigerating machine used to transfer heat between fluids. Chillers are either direct expansion with a compressor or absorption type.

Setpoint.label: Setpoint
Setpoint.description: A Setpoint is an input value at which the desired property is set

Active_Chilled_Beam.label: Active Chilled Beam
Active_Chilled_Beam.description: A Chilled Beam with an integral primary air connection that induces air flow through the device.

Chilled_Beam.label: Chilled Beam
Chilled_Beam.description: A device with an integrated coil that performs sensible heating of a space via circulation of room air. Chilled Beams are not designed to perform latent cooling; see Induction Units. Despite their name, Chilled Beams may perform heating or cooling of a space depending on their configuration.

Terminal_Unit.label: Terminal Unit
Terminal_Unit.description: A device that regulates the volumetric flow rate and/or the temperature of the controlled medium.

Active_Power_Sensor.label: Active Power Sensor
Active_Power_Sensor.description: Measures the portion of power that, averaged over a complete cycle of the AC waveform, results in net transfer of energy in one direction

Electric_Power_Sensor.label: Electric Power Sensor
Electric_Power_Sensor.description: Measures the amount of instantaneous electric power consumed

Power_Sensor.label: Power Sensor
Power_Sensor.description: Measures the amount of instantaneous power consumed

Air_Cooled_Chiller.label: Air Cooled Chiller
Air_Cooled_Chiller.description: A chiller that uses air to cool the refrigerant, used in various commercial and industrial cooling applications

Air_Flow_Loss_Alarm.label: Air Flow Loss Alarm
Air_Flow_Loss_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates loss in air flow.

Air_Flow_Alarm.label: Air Flow Alarm
Air_Flow_Alarm.description: An alarm related to air flow.

Alarm.label: Alarm
Alarm.description: Alarm points are signals (either audible or visual) that alert an operator to an off-normal condition which requires some form of corrective action

Air_Loop.label: Air Loop
Air_Loop.description: The set of connected equipment serving one path of air

Loop.label: Loop
Loop.description: A collection of connected equipment; part of a System

Alarm_Delay_Parameter.label: Alarm Delay Parameter
Alarm_Delay_Parameter.description: A parameter determining how long to delay an alarm after sufficient conditions have been met

Delay_Parameter.label: Delay Parameter
Delay_Parameter.description: A parameter determining how long to delay a subsequent action to take place after a received signal

Parameter.label: Parameter
Parameter.description: Parameter points are configuration settings used to guide the operation of equipment and control systems; for example they may provide bounds on valid setpoint values

Air_Quality_Sensor.label: Air Quality Sensor
Air_Quality_Sensor.description: A sensor which provides a measure of air quality

Common_Space.label: Common Space
Common_Space.description: A class of spaces that are used by multiple people at the same time

Audio_Visual_Equipment.label: Audio Visual Equipment
Audio_Visual_Equipment.description: Equipment related to sound and visual components such as speakers and displays.

ICT_Equipment.label: ICT Equipment
ICT_Equipment.description: Information and Communications Technology (ICT) equipment operates with a processor to process data or logic and create digital signals.

Automatic_Mode_Command.label: Automatic Mode Command
Automatic_Mode_Command.description: Controls whether or not a device or controller is operating in "Automatic" mode

Mode_Command.label: Mode Command
Mode_Command.description: Controls the operating mode of a device or controller

Command.label: Command
Command.description: A Command is an output point that directly determines the behavior of equipment and/or affects relevant operational points.

Automatic_Tint_Window_Array.label: Automatic Tint Window Array
Automatic_Tint_Window_Array.description: An array of Automatic Tint Windows.

System.label: System
System.description: A System is a combination of equipment and auxiliary devices (e.g., controls, accessories, interconnecting means, and termi­nal elements) by which energy is transformed so it performs a specific function such as HVAC, service water heating, or lighting. (ASHRAE Dictionary).

Automatic_Transfer_Switch.label: Automatic Transfer Switch
Automatic_Transfer_Switch.description: An automatic transfer switch (ATS) is a device that automatically transfers a power supply from its primary source to a backup source when it senses a failure or outage in the primary source.

Automatic_Switch.label: Automatic Switch
Automatic_Switch.description: An automatic switch operates automatically in the event of some current threshold or other designed event. Criteria for automatic operation is generally a physical property of the switch.

Switchgear.label: Switchgear
Switchgear.description: A main disconnect or service disconnect feeds power to a switchgear, which then distributes power to the rest of the building through smaller amperage-rated disconnects.

Transfer_Switch.label: Transfer Switch
Transfer_Switch.description: An electrical switch that switches a load between two (or more) sources.

Availability_Status.label: Availability Status
Availability_Status.description: Indicates if a piece of equipment, system, or functionality is available for operation

Status.label: Status
Status.description: A Status is input point that reports the current operating mode, state, position, or condition of an item. Statuses are observations and should be considered 'read-only'

Average_Cooling_Demand_Sensor.label: Average Cooling Demand Sensor
Average_Cooling_Demand_Sensor.description: Measures the average power consumed by a cooling process as the amount of power consumed over some interval

Cooling_Demand_Sensor.label: Cooling Demand Sensor
Cooling_Demand_Sensor.description: Measures the amount of power consumed by a cooling process; typically found by multiplying the tonnage of a unit (e.g. RTU) by the efficiency rating in kW/ton

Demand_Sensor.label: Demand Sensor
Demand_Sensor.description: Measures the amount of power consumed by the use of some process; typically found by multiplying the tonnage of a unit (e.g. RTU) by the efficiency rating in kW/ton

Average_Exhaust_Air_Static_Pressure_Sens.label: Average Exhaust Air Static Pressure Sensor
Average_Exhaust_Air_Static_Pressure_Sens.description: The computed average static pressure of air in exhaust regions of an HVAC system over some period of time

Exhaust_Air_Static_Pressure_Sensor.label: Exhaust Air Static Pressure Sensor
Exhaust_Air_Static_Pressure_Sensor.description: The static pressure of air within exhaust regions of an HVAC system

Air_Static_Pressure_Sensor.label: Air Static Pressure Sensor
Air_Static_Pressure_Sensor.description: Measures the pressure exerted by the air in a system, not influenced by its motion.

Static_Pressure_Sensor.label: Static Pressure Sensor
Static_Pressure_Sensor.description: Measures resistance to airflow in a heating and cooling system's components and duct work

Pressure_Sensor.label: Pressure Sensor
Pressure_Sensor.description: Measure the amount of force acting on a unit area

Average_Heating_Demand_Sensor.label: Average Heating Demand Sensor
Average_Heating_Demand_Sensor.description: Measures the average power consumed by a heating process as the amount of power consumed over some interval

Heating_Demand_Sensor.label: Heating Demand Sensor
Heating_Demand_Sensor.description: Measures the amount of power consumed by a heating process; typically found by multiplying the tonnage of a unit (e.g. RTU) by the efficiency rating in kW/ton

Average_Zone_Air_Temperature_Sensor.label: Average Zone Air Temperature Sensor
Average_Zone_Air_Temperature_Sensor.description: The computed average temperature of air in a zone, over some period of time

Zone_Air_Temperature_Sensor.label: Zone Air Temperature Sensor
Zone_Air_Temperature_Sensor.description: A physical or virtual sensor which represents the temperature of an HVAC Zone

Temperature_Sensor.label: Temperature Sensor
Temperature_Sensor.description: Measures temperature: the physical property of matter that quantitatively expresses the common notions of hot and cold

Backflow_Preventer_Valve.label: Backflow Preventer Valve
Backflow_Preventer_Valve.description: Valve designed to prevent the reverse flow of fluid, typically water, thereby protecting potable water supplies from contamination or pollution.

Check_Valve.label: Check Valve
Check_Valve.description: Valve that allows fluid to flow in only one direction, preventing reverse flow.

Valve.label: Valve
Valve.description: A device that regulates, directs or controls the flow of a fluid by opening, closing or partially obstructing various passageways

Basement.label: Basement
Basement.description: The floor of a building which is partly or entirely below ground level.

Floor.label: Floor
Floor.description: A level, typically representing a horizontal aggregation of spaces that are vertically bound. (referring to IFC)

Battery.label: Battery
Battery.description: A container that stores chemical energy that can be converted into electricity and used as a source of power

Energy_Storage.label: Energy Storage
Energy_Storage.description: Devices or equipment that store energy in its various forms

Battery_Energy_Storage_System.label: Battery Energy Storage System
Battery_Energy_Storage_System.description: A collection of batteries that provides energy storage, along with their supporting equipment

Energy_Storage_System.label: Energy Storage System
Energy_Storage_System.description: A collection of devices that stores electricity

Energy_System.label: Energy System
Energy_System.description: A collection of devices that generates, stores or transports electricity

Electrical_System.label: Electrical System
Electrical_System.description: Devices that serve or are part of the electrical subsystem in the building

Battery_Room.label: Battery Room
Battery_Room.description: A room used to hold batteries for backup power

Electrical_Room.label: Electrical Room
Electrical_Room.description: A class of service rooms that house electrical equipment for a building

Service_Room.label: Service Room
Service_Room.description: A class of spaces related to the operations of building subsystems, e.g. HVAC, electrical, IT, plumbing, etc

Battery_Voltage_Sensor.label: Battery Voltage Sensor
Battery_Voltage_Sensor.description: Measures the capacity of a battery

Voltage_Sensor.label: Voltage Sensor
Voltage_Sensor.description: Measures the voltage of an electrical device or object

Bench_Space.label: Bench Space
Bench_Space.description: For areas of play in a stadium, the area for partcipants and referees by the side of the field

Outdoor_Area.label: Outdoor Area
Outdoor_Area.description: A class of spaces that exist outside of a building

Blind_Group.label: Blind Group
Blind_Group.description: A group of Blinds commonly attached to a single controller.

Shading_System.label: Shading System
Shading_System.description: Devices that can control daylighting through various means

Boiler_Command.label: Boiler Command
Boiler_Command.description: A command to control a boiler

Booster_Fan.label: Booster Fan
Booster_Fan.description: Fan activated to increase airflow beyond what is provided by the default configuration

Fan.label: Fan
Fan.description: Any device with two or more blades or vanes attached to a rotating shaft used to produce an airflow for the purpose of comfort, ventilation, exhaust, heating, cooling, or any other gaseous transport.

Branch_Selector.label: Branch Selector
Branch_Selector.description: A device in VRF systems that regulates the flow of refrigerant to different indoor units or branches, ensuring optimal distribution of heating or cooling according to the specific requirements of each zone or area in the building.

Breaker_Panel.label: Breaker Panel
Breaker_Panel.description: Breaker Panel distributes power into various end-uses.

Broadcast_Room.label: Broadcast Room
Broadcast_Room.description: A space to organize and manage a broadcast. Separate from studio

Media_Room.label: Media Room
Media_Room.description: A class of spaces related to the creation of media

Building_Air_Humidity_Setpoint.label: Building Air Humidity Setpoint
Building_Air_Humidity_Setpoint.description: Setpoint for humidity in a building

Building_Air_Static_Pressure_Sensor.label: Building Air Static Pressure Sensor
Building_Air_Static_Pressure_Sensor.description: The static pressure of air within a building

Building_Air_Static_Pressure_Setpoint.label: Building Air Static Pressure Setpoint
Building_Air_Static_Pressure_Setpoint.description: Sets static pressure of the entire building

Building_Chilled_Water_Meter.label: Building Chilled Water Meter
Building_Chilled_Water_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water of a whole building

Building_Meter.label: Building Meter
Building_Meter.description: A meter that measures usage or consumption of some media for a whole building

Meter.label: Meter
Meter.description: A device that measure usage or consumption of some media --- typically a form energy or power.

Chilled_Water_Meter.label: Chilled Water Meter
Chilled_Water_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water

Water_Meter.label: Water Meter
Water_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water

Disconnect_Switch.label: Disconnect Switch
Disconnect_Switch.description: A disconnect switch performs the task of manually cutting or reconnecting power from an electrical supply by creating or closing an air insulation gap between two conduction points. Also known as an 'Isolation Switch'.

Building_Electrical_Meter.label: Building Electrical Meter
Building_Electrical_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity of a whole building

Electrical_Meter.label: Electrical Meter
Electrical_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity

Building_Gas_Meter.label: Building Gas Meter
Building_Gas_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas of a whole building

Gas_Meter.label: Gas Meter
Gas_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas

Building_Hot_Water_Meter.label: Building Hot Water Meter
Building_Hot_Water_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water of a whole building

Hot_Water_Meter.label: Hot Water Meter
Hot_Water_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water

Building_Water_Meter.label: Building Water Meter
Building_Water_Meter.description: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water of a whole building

Bus_Riser.label: Bus Riser
Bus_Riser.description: Bus Risers are commonly fed from a switchgear and rise up through a series of floors to the main power distribution source for each floor.

Bypass_Air_Flow_Sensor.label: Bypass Air Flow Sensor
Bypass_Air_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of bypass air

Air_Flow_Sensor.label: Air Flow Sensor
Air_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of air

Flow_Sensor.label: Flow Sensor
Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of some substance

Bypass_Damper.label: Bypass Damper
Bypass_Damper.description: A bypass damper is a type of damper that is employed in forced-air bypass applications to reduce the buildup of static pressure, usually when certain zone dampers are closed.

Damper.label: Damper
Damper.description: Element inserted into an air-distribution system or element of an air-distribution system permitting modification of the air resistance of the system and consequently changing the airflow rate or shutting off the airflow.

Bypass_Water_Flow_Sensor.label: Bypass Water Flow Sensor
Bypass_Water_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of bypass water

Water_Flow_Sensor.label: Water Flow Sensor
Water_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of water

Bypass_Water_Flow_Setpoint.label: Bypass Water Flow Setpoint
Bypass_Water_Flow_Setpoint.description: Sets the target flow rate of bypass water

Water_Flow_Setpoint.label: Water Flow Setpoint
Water_Flow_Setpoint.description: Sets the target flow rate of water

CO2_Alarm_Sensitivity_Parameter.label: CO2 Alarm Sensitivity Parameter
CO2_Alarm_Sensitivity_Parameter.description: A parameter indicates the sensitivity to activate a CO2 alarm.

Alarm_Sensitivity_Parameter.label: Alarm Sensitivity Parameter
Alarm_Sensitivity_Parameter.description: A parameter indicates the sensitivity to activate an alarm.

CO2_Differential_Sensor.label: CO2 Differential Sensor
CO2_Differential_Sensor.description: Measures the difference between CO2 levels of inside and outside air

CO2_Sensor.label: CO2 Sensor
CO2_Sensor.description: Measures properties of CO2 in air

Cafeteria.label: Cafeteria
Cafeteria.description: A space to serve food and beverages

Capillary_Tube_Metering_Device.label: Capillary Tube Metering Device
Capillary_Tube_Metering_Device.description: A fixed orifice device in refrigeration systems that controls refrigerant flow based on its diameter and length, without moving parts

Refrigerant_Metering_Device.label: Refrigerant Metering Device
Refrigerant_Metering_Device.description: Responsible for regulating refrigerant flow, which includes mechanisms like TXVs, EXVs, and capillary tubes

Cassette_Fan_Coil_Unit.label: Cassette Fan Coil Unit
Cassette_Fan_Coil_Unit.description: A type of fan coil unit installed within the ceiling void, typically using a cassette for air delivery

Fan_Coil_Unit.label: Fan Coil Unit
Fan_Coil_Unit.description: Terminal device consisting of a heating and/or cooling heat exchanger or 'coil' and fan that is used to control the temperature in the space where it is installed

Ceiling_Fan.label: Ceiling Fan
Ceiling_Fan.description: A fan installed on the ceiling of a room for the purpose of air circulation

Centrifugal_Chiller.label: Centrifugal Chiller
Centrifugal_Chiller.description: A chiller that uses the vapor compression cycle to chill water. It throws off the heat collected from the chilled water plus the heat from the compressor to a water loop

Change_Filter_Alarm.label: Change Filter Alarm
Change_Filter_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates that a filter must be changed

Chilled_Water_Booster_Pump.label: Chilled Water Booster Pump
Chilled_Water_Booster_Pump.description: Used to increase the pressure and flow of chilled water in a system to ensure adequate supply where needed.

Booster_Pump.label: Booster Pump
Booster_Pump.description: Used to increase the pressure and flow of a fluid, typically water, in a system to ensure adequate supply where needed.

Pump.label: Pump
Pump.description: Machine for imparting energy to a fluid, causing it to do work, drawing a fluid into itself through an entrance port, and forcing the fluid out through an exhaust port.

Chilled_Water_Pump.label: Chilled Water Pump
Chilled_Water_Pump.description: A pump that performs work on chilled water; typically part of a chilled water system

Water_Pump.label: Water Pump
Water_Pump.description: A pump that performs work on water

Chilled_Water_Circulator_Pump.label: Chilled Water Circulator Pump
Chilled_Water_Circulator_Pump.description: Used to move chilled water in a closed circuit, ensuring continuous flow.

Circulator_Pump.label: Circulator Pump
Circulator_Pump.description: Used to move hot or cold water in a closed circuit, ensuring continuous fluid flow.

Chilled_Water_Coil.label: Chilled Water Coil
Chilled_Water_Coil.description: A cooling element made of pipe or tube that removes heat from equipment, machines or airflows that is filled with chilled water.

Cooling_Coil.label: Cooling Coil
Cooling_Coil.description: A cooling element made of pipe or tube that removes heat from equipment, machines or airflows. Typically filled with either refrigerant or cold water.

Coil.label: Coil
Coil.description: Cooling or heating element made of pipe or tube that may or may not be finned and formed into helical or serpentine shape (ASHRAE Dictionary)

Heat_Exchanger.label: Heat Exchanger
Heat_Exchanger.description: A heat exchanger is a piece of equipment built for efficient heat transfer from one medium to another. The media may be separated by a solid wall to prevent mixing or they may be in direct contact (BEDES)

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Dead.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Deadband Setpoint
Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Dead.description: Sets the size of a deadband of differential pressure of chilled water

Differential_Pressure_Deadband_Setpoint.label: Differential Pressure Deadband Setpoint
Differential_Pressure_Deadband_Setpoint.description: Sets the size of a deadband of differential pressure

Differential_Setpoint.label: Differential Setpoint
Differential_Setpoint.description: A type of Setpoints that is related to the difference between two measurements

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Inte.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Integral Time Parameter

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Load.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Load Shed Reset Status
Chilled Water Differential Pressure Load Shed Status

Load_Shed_Status.label: Load Shed Status
Load_Shed_Status.description: Indicates if a load shedding policy is in effect

Pressure_Status.label: Pressure Status
Pressure_Status.description: Indicates if pressure is within expected bounds

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Load.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Load Shed Setpoint

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Setp.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Setpoint
Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Setp.description: Sets the target water differential pressure between an upstream and downstream point in a water pipe or conduit used to carry chilled water

Water_Differential_Pressure_Setpoint.label: Water Differential Pressure Setpoint
Water_Differential_Pressure_Setpoint.description: Sets the target water differential pressure between an upstream and downstream point in a water pipe or conduit

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Prop.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Proportional Band Parameter

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Sens.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Sensor
Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Sens.description: Measures the difference in water pressure on either side of a chilled water valve

Water_Differential_Pressure_Sensor.label: Water Differential Pressure Sensor
Water_Differential_Pressure_Sensor.description: Measures the difference in water pressure between two points in a system.

Differential_Pressure_Sensor.label: Differential Pressure Sensor
Differential_Pressure_Sensor.description: Measures the difference between two applied pressures

Chilled_Water_Differential_Pressure_Step.label: Chilled Water Differential Pressure Step Parameter

Chilled_Water_Differential_Temperature_S.label: Chilled Water Differential Temperature Sensor
Chilled_Water_Differential_Temperature_S.description: Measures the difference in temperature between the entering water to the chiller or other water cooling device and leaving water from the same chiller or other water cooling device

Chilled_Water_Temperature_Sensor.label: Chilled Water Temperature Sensor
Chilled_Water_Temperature_Sensor.description: Measures the temperature of chilled water

Return_Air_Differential_Pressure_Setpoin.description: Sets the target air differential pressure between an upstream and downstream point in a return air duct or conduit

Return_Air_Enthalpy_Sensor.label: Return Air Enthalpy Sensor
Return_Air_Enthalpy_Sensor.description: Measures the total heat content of return air

Return_Air_Flow_Sensor.label: Return Air Flow Sensor
Return_Air_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of return air

Return_Air_Grains_Sensor.label: Return Air Grains Sensor
Return_Air_Grains_Sensor.description: Measures the mass of water vapor in return air

Return_Air_Humidity_Sensor.label: Return Air Humidity Sensor
Return_Air_Humidity_Sensor.description: Measures the relative humidity of return air

Return_Air_Plenum.label: Return Air Plenum
Return_Air_Plenum.description: A component of the HVAC the receives air from the room to recirculate or exhaust to or from the building

Air_Plenum.label: Air Plenum
Air_Plenum.description: A component of the HVAC the receives air from the air handling unit or room to distribute or exhaust to or from the building

Return_Air_Temperature_High_Reset_Setpoi.label: Return Air Temperature High Reset Setpoint

Return_Air_Temperature_Sensor.label: Return Air Temperature Sensor
Return_Air_Temperature_Sensor.description: Measures the temperature of return air

Return_Damper.label: Return Damper
Return_Damper.description: A damper that modulates the flow of return air

Return_Fan.label: Return Fan
Return_Fan.description: Fan moving return air -- air that is circulated from the building back into the HVAC system

Return_Heating_Valve.label: Return Heating Valve
Return_Heating_Valve.description: A valve installed on the return side of a heat exchanger

Refrigerant_Valve.label: Refrigerant Valve
Refrigerant_Valve.description: A valve controlling the flow or pressure of refrigerant in refrigeration or air conditioning systems, crucial for system efficiency

Riser.label: Riser
Riser.description: A vertical shaft indented for installing building infrastructure e.g., electrical wire, network communication wire, plumbing, etc

Vertical_Space.label: Vertical Space
Vertical_Space.description: A class of spaces used to connect multiple floors or levels..

Run_Request_Status.label: Run Request Status
Run_Request_Status.description: Indicates if a request has been filed to start a device or equipment

Sash_Position_Sensor.label: Sash Position Sensor
Sash_Position_Sensor.description: Measures the current position of a sash in terms of the percent of fully open

Schedule_Temperature_Setpoint.label: Schedule Temperature Setpoint
Schedule_Temperature_Setpoint.description: The current setpoint as indicated by the schedule

Failure_Alarm.label: Failure Alarm
Failure_Alarm.description: Alarms that indicate the failure of devices, equipment, systems and control loops

Shared_Office.label: Shared Office
Shared_Office.description: An office used by multiple people

Short_Cycle_Alarm.label: Short Cycle Alarm
Short_Cycle_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates a short cycle occurred. A short cycle occurs when a cooling cycle is prevented from completing its full cycle

Cycle_Alarm.label: Cycle Alarm
Cycle_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates off-normal conditions associated with HVAC cycles

Shower.label: Shower
Shower.description: A space containing showers, usually adjacent to an athletic or execise area

Solar_Azimuth_Angle_Sensor.label: Solar Azimuth Angle Sensor
Solar_Azimuth_Angle_Sensor.description: Measures the azimuth angle of the sun

Angle_Sensor.label: Angle Sensor
Angle_Sensor.description: Measues the planar angle of some phenomenon

Solar_Zenith_Angle_Sensor.label: Solar Zenith Angle Sensor
Solar_Zenith_Angle_Sensor.description: Measures the zenith angle of the sun

Space_Heater.label: Space Heater
Space_Heater.description: A heater used to warm the air in an enclosed area, such as a room or office

Speed_Command.label: Speed Command
Speed_Command.description: A command to set speed to a certain degree.

Sports_Service_Room.label: Sports Service Room
Sports_Service_Room.description: A class of spaces used in the support of sports

Stage_Enable_Command.label: Stage Enable Command
Stage_Enable_Command.description: A point representing a discrete stage which the equipment should be operating at. The desired stage number should be identified by an entity property

Stage_Riser.label: Stage Riser
Stage_Riser.description: A low platform in a space or on a stage

Stages_Status.label: Stages Status
Stages_Status.description: Indicates which stage a control loop or equipment is in

Standby_CRAC.label: Standby CRAC
Standby_CRAC.description: A CRAC that is activated as part of a lead/lag operation or when an alarm occurs in a primary unit

Computer_Room_Air_Conditioning.label: Computer Room Air Conditioning
Computer_Room_Air_Conditioning.description: A device that monitors and maintains the temperature, air distribution and humidity in a network room or data center.

Standby_Cooling_Zone_Air_Temperature_Set.label: Standby Cooling Zone Air Temperature Setpoint

Cooling_Zone_Air_Temperature_Setpoint.label: Cooling Zone Air Temperature Setpoint
Cooling_Zone_Air_Temperature_Setpoint.description: The cooling setpoint for a specific zone in a building.

Standby_Fan.label: Standby Fan
Standby_Fan.description: Fan that is activated as part of a lead/lag operation or when a primary fan raises an alarm

Standby_Glycool_Unit_On_Off_Status.label: Standby Glycool Unit On Off Status
Standby_Glycool_Unit_On_Off_Status.description: Indicates the on/off status of a standby glycool unit

Standby_Unit_On_Off_Status.label: Standby Unit On Off Status
Standby_Unit_On_Off_Status.description: Indicates the on/off status of a standby unit

Standby_Heating_Zone_Air_Temperature_Set.label: Standby Heating Zone Air Temperature Setpoint

Heating_Zone_Air_Temperature_Setpoint.label: Heating Zone Air Temperature Setpoint
Heating_Zone_Air_Temperature_Setpoint.description: The heating setpoint for a specific zone in a building.

Standby_Target_Zone_Air_Temperature_Setp.label: Standby Target Zone Air Temperature Setpoint

Start_Stop_Command.label: Start Stop Command
Start_Stop_Command.description: A Start/Stop Command controls or reports the active/inactive status of a control sequence

Static_Transfer_Switch.label: Static Transfer Switch
Static_Transfer_Switch.description: Similar to ATS, but utilises no moving parts in the switch to achieve much faster response times.

Steam_Baseboard_Radiator.label: Steam Baseboard Radiator
Steam_Baseboard_Radiator.description: Steam heating device located at or near the floor

Steam_Distribution.label: Steam Distribution
Steam_Distribution.description: Utilize a steam distribution source to represent how steam is distributed across multiple destinations

Steam_Pressure_Reducing_Valve.label: Steam Pressure Reducing Valve
Steam_Pressure_Reducing_Valve.description: Valve designed to reduce steam pressure from a high to a manageable level; maintains uniform steam outlet pressure.

Pressure_Reducing_Valve.label: Pressure Reducing Valve
Pressure_Reducing_Valve.description: Valve used to reduce a high supply pressure to a usable level; maintains uniform outlet pressure despite inlet pressure variation.

Steam_Pressure_Relief_Valve.label: Steam Pressure Relief Valve
Steam_Pressure_Relief_Valve.description: Valve designed to automatically relieve excessive steam pressure.

Pressure_Relief_Valve.label: Pressure Relief Valve
Pressure_Relief_Valve.description: Pressure-actuated valve to automatically relieve excessive pressure; prevents explosive shattering of the housing.

Steam_System.label: Steam System
Steam_System.description: The equipment, devices and conduits that handle the production and distribution of steam in a building

Steam_Usage_Sensor.label: Steam Usage Sensor
Steam_Usage_Sensor.description: Measures the amount of steam that is consumed or used, over some period of time

Studio.label: Studio
Studio.description: A room used for the production or media, usually with either a specialized set or a specialized sound booth for recording

Switch_Room.label: Switch Room
Switch_Room.description: A telecommuncations room housing network switches

System_Shutdown_Status.label: System Shutdown Status
System_Shutdown_Status.description: Indicates if a system has been shutdown

TETRA_Room.label: TETRA Room
TETRA_Room.description: A room used for local two-way radio networks, e.g. the portable radios carried by facilities staff

TVOC_Level_Sensor.label: TVOC Level Sensor
TVOC_Level_Sensor.description: A sensor measuring the level of all VOCs in air

Tablet.label: Tablet
Tablet.description: A flat, handheld mobile computer, usually with a touchscreen

Team_Room.label: Team Room
Team_Room.description: An office used by multiple team members for specific work tasks. Distinct from Conference Room

Adjust_Sensor.label: Adjust Sensor
Adjust_Sensor.description: Measures user-provided adjustment of some value

Temperature_Alarm_Sensitivity_Parameter.label: Temperature Alarm Sensitivity Parameter
Temperature_Alarm_Sensitivity_Parameter.description: A parameter indicates the sensitivity to activate a temperature alarm.

Temperature_Tolerance_Parameter.label: Temperature Tolerance Parameter
Temperature_Tolerance_Parameter.description: A parameter determining the difference between upper and lower limits of temperature.

Temporary_Occupancy_Status.label: Temporary Occupancy Status
Temporary_Occupancy_Status.description: For systems that differentiate between scheduled occupied/unoccupied mode, this indicates if a space is temporarily occupied when it would otherwise be unoccupied

Occupancy_Status.label: Occupancy Status
Occupancy_Status.description: Indicates if a room or space is occupied

Thermal_Energy_Usage_Sensor.label: Thermal Energy Usage Sensor
Thermal_Energy_Usage_Sensor.description: A sensor that records the quantity of thermal energy consumed in a given period

Thermal_Expansion_Valve.label: Thermal Expansion Valve
Thermal_Expansion_Valve.description: An type of metering device that automatically adjusts refrigerant flow based on temperature changes, using a sensing bulb

Sensor_Equipment.label: Sensor Equipment
Sensor_Equipment.description: A piece of equipment for sensing some physical properties

Thermostatic_Mixing_Valve.label: Thermostatic Mixing Valve
Thermostatic_Mixing_Valve.description: A valve that blends hot water with cold water to ensure constant, safe shower and bath outlet temperatures, preventing scalding.

Ticketing_Booth.label: Ticketing Booth
Ticketing_Booth.description: A room or space used to sell or distribute tickets to events at a venue

Tint_Command.label: Tint Command
Tint_Command.description: The target level of window tint.

Tint_Status.label: Tint Status
Tint_Status.description: The current level of window tint, errors, or transient states.

Touchpanel.label: Touchpanel
Touchpanel.description: A switch used to operate all or part of a lighting installation that uses a touch-based mechanism (typically resistive or capacitive) rather than a mechanical actuator

Transfer_Fan.label: Transfer Fan
Transfer_Fan.description: A fan that transfers air from a space to another space.

Transformer.label: Transformer
Transformer.description: A Transformer is usually fed by a high-voltage source and then steps down the voltage to a lower-voltage feed for low-voltage application (such as lights). Transformers also can step up voltage, but this generally does not apply to in building distribution.

Transformer_Room.label: Transformer Room
Transformer_Room.description: An electrical room where electricity enters and is transformed to different voltages and currents by the equipment contained in the room

Tunnel.label: Tunnel
Tunnel.description: An enclosed space that connects buildings. Often underground

Underfloor_Air_Plenum.label: Underfloor Air Plenum
Underfloor_Air_Plenum.description: An open space between a structural concrete slab and the underside of a raised access floor system that connects to an air handling unit to receive conditioned and/or ventilating air before delivery to the room(s)

Supply_Air_Plenum.label: Supply Air Plenum
Supply_Air_Plenum.description: A component of the HVAC the receives air from the air handling unit to distribute to the building

Underfloor_Air_Plenum_Static_Pressure_Se.label: Underfloor Air Plenum Static Pressure Sensor
Underfloor_Air_Plenum_Static_Pressure_Se.description: Measures the outward push of air against the plenum surfaces and used to measure the resistance when air moves through the plenum

Underfloor_Air_Plenum_Static_Pressure_Se.label: Underfloor Air Plenum Static Pressure Setpoint
Underfloor_Air_Plenum_Static_Pressure_Se.description: Sets the underfloor air plenum static pressure

Underfloor_Air_Temperature_Sensor.label: Underfloor Air Temperature Sensor
Underfloor_Air_Temperature_Sensor.description: Measures the temperature of underfloor air

Unit_Failure_Alarm.label: Unit Failure Alarm
Unit_Failure_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates the failure of an equipment or device

Unoccupied_Air_Temperature_Setpoint.label: Unoccupied Air Temperature Setpoint
Unoccupied_Air_Temperature_Setpoint.description: Sets temperature of air when unoccupied

Unoccupied_Cooling_Mode_Status.label: Unoccupied Cooling Mode Status
Unoccupied_Cooling_Mode_Status.description: Indicates whether a system, device or control loop is in an unoccupied cooling mode

Unoccupied_Heating_Mode_Status.label: Unoccupied Heating Mode Status
Unoccupied_Heating_Mode_Status.description: Indicates whether a system, device or control loop is in an unoccupied heating mode

Unoccupied_Humidity_Setpoint.label: Unoccupied Humidity Setpoint
Unoccupied_Humidity_Setpoint.description: Target humidity level when the location is unoccupied.

VFD_Enable_Command.label: VFD Enable Command
VFD_Enable_Command.description: Enables operation of a variable frequency drive

Valve_Position_Alarm.label: Valve Position Alarm
Valve_Position_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates that the valve position is not in a normal state.

Valve_Position_Command.label: Valve Position Command
Valve_Position_Command.description: Controls the position (the degree of openness) of a valve

Valve_Command.label: Valve Command
Valve_Command.description: Controls or reports the openness of a valve (typically as a proportion of its full range of motion)

Valve_Position_Sensor.label: Valve Position Sensor
Valve_Position_Sensor.description: Measures the current position of a valve in terms of the percent of fully open

Valve_Status.label: Valve Status
Valve_Status.description: The current status of the valve.

Vent_Operating_Mode_Status.label: Vent Operating Mode Status
Vent_Operating_Mode_Status.description: Indicates the current operating mode of a vent

Operating_Mode_Status.label: Operating Mode Status
Operating_Mode_Status.description: Indicates the current operating mode of a system, device or control loop

Ventilation_Air_Flow_Ratio_Limit.label: Ventilation Air Flow Ratio Limit
Ventilation_Air_Flow_Ratio_Limit.description: A parameter that places a lower or upper bound on the range of permitted values of a Ventilation_Air_Flow_Ratio_Setpoint.

Ventilation_Air_System.label: Ventilation Air System
Ventilation_Air_System.description: The equipment, devices, and conduits that handle the introduction and distribution of ventilation air in the building

Air_System.label: Air System
Air_System.description: The equipment, distribution systems and terminals that introduce or exhaust, either collectively or individually, the air into and from the building

Visitor_Lobby.label: Visitor Lobby
Visitor_Lobby.description: A lobby for visitors to the building. Sometimes used to distinguish from an employee entrance looby

Voltage_Imbalance_Sensor.label: Voltage Imbalance Sensor
Voltage_Imbalance_Sensor.description: A sensor which measures the voltage difference (imbalance) between phases of an electrical system

Voltage_Ratio_Setpoint.label: Voltage Ratio Setpoint
Voltage_Ratio_Setpoint.description: Sets the ratio of voltage in a transformer

Wall_Air_Conditioner.label: Wall Air Conditioner
Wall_Air_Conditioner.description: A wall air conditioner, also known as a window air conditioner when installed in a window frame, is a self-contained unit that cools a room by drawing in warm air, cooling it over a refrigerant coil, and recirculating it back into the space.

Wall_Fan_Coil_Unit.label: Wall Fan Coil Unit
Wall_Fan_Coil_Unit.description: A wall-mounted fan coil unit used for individual room heating and cooling, often found in hotels, apartments, and offices

Wardrobe.label: Wardrobe
Wardrobe.description: Storage for clothing, costumes, or uniforms

Warm_Cool_Adjust_Sensor.label: Warm Cool Adjust Sensor
Warm_Cool_Adjust_Sensor.description: User provided adjustment of zone temperature, typically in the range of +/- 5 degrees

Warmest_Zone_Air_Temperature_Sensor.label: Warmest Zone Air Temperature Sensor
Warmest_Zone_Air_Temperature_Sensor.description: The zone temperature that is warmest; drives the supply temperature of cold air. A computed value rather than a physical sensor. Also referred to as a 'Highest Zone Air Temperature Sensor'

Waste_Amount_Sensor.label: Waste Amount Sensor
Waste_Amount_Sensor.description: A metric used for measuring the quantity of waste generated in a building.

Waste_Meter.label: Waste Meter
Waste_Meter.description: A Waste Meter is used for tracking and categorizing various waste types in a building, aiding in waste management facilitating waste reduction, recycling, and disposal strategies.

Waste_Storage.label: Waste Storage
Waste_Storage.description: A room used for storing waste such as trash or recycling

Water_Cooled_Chiller.label: Water Cooled Chiller
Water_Cooled_Chiller.description: A chiller system using water in the heat exchange process, employed in industrial or commercial facilities for cooling

Water_Differential_Temperature_Setpoint.description: Sets the target differential temperature between the start and end of a heat transfer cycle in a water circuit

Water_Distribution.description: Utilize a water distribution source to represent how water is distributed across multiple destinations (pipes)

Water_Loss_Alarm.label: Water Loss Alarm
Water_Loss_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates a loss of water e.g. during transport

Water_Pressure_Reducing_Valve.label: Water Pressure Reducing Valve

Water_Pressure_Relief_Valve.label: Water Pressure Relief Valve
Water_Pressure_Relief_Valve.description: Valve designed to automatically relieve excessive water pressure.

Water_Tank.label: Water Tank
Water_Tank.description: A space used to hold water. This will likely be deprecated in future releases of Brick for the sake of clarity w.r.t. equipment classification of tanks

Wind_Direction_Sensor.label: Wind Direction Sensor
Wind_Direction_Sensor.description: Measures the direction of wind in degrees relative to North

Direction_Sensor.label: Direction Sensor
Direction_Sensor.description: Measures the direction in degrees in which a phenomenon is occuring

Wind_Speed_Sensor.label: Wind Speed Sensor
Wind_Speed_Sensor.description: Measured speed of wind, caused by air moving from high to low pressure

Zone_Air_Conditioning_Mode_Status.label: Zone Air Conditioning Mode Status
Zone_Air_Conditioning_Mode_Status.description: Indicates the mode of AC for a zone

Zone_Air_Cooling_Temperature_Setpoint.label: Zone Air Cooling Temperature Setpoint
Zone_Air_Cooling_Temperature_Setpoint.description: The upper (cooling) setpoint for zone air temperature

Zone_Air_Heating_Temperature_Setpoint.label: Zone Air Heating Temperature Setpoint
Zone_Air_Heating_Temperature_Setpoint.description: The lower (heating) setpoint for zone air temperature

Zone_Air_Humidity_Sensor.label: Zone Air Humidity Sensor
Zone_Air_Humidity_Sensor.description: Measures the relative humidity of zone air

Zone_CO2_Level_Sensor.description: A physical or virtual sensor which represents the CO2 level of an HVAC Zone

CO2_Level_Sensor.description: Measures the concentration of CO2 in air

Zone_Damper.label: Zone Damper
Zone_Damper.description: Dampers open and close to regulate zone temperatures in an HVAC system.

Load_Shed_Command.label: Load Shed Command
Load_Shed_Command.description: Controls load shedding behavior provided by a control system

AHU.label: AHU
AHU.description: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Air_Handler_Unit.label: Air Handler Unit
Air_Handler_Unit.description: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Average_Discharge_Air_Flow_Sensor.label: Average Discharge Air Flow Sensor
Average_Discharge_Air_Flow_Sensor.description: The computed average flow of discharge air over some interval

Supply_Air_Flow_Sensor.label: Supply Air Flow Sensor
Supply_Air_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of supply air

Breakroom.label: Breakroom
Breakroom.description: A space for people to relax while not working

CRAH.label: CRAH
CRAH.description: a computer room air handler (CRAH) uses fans, cooling coils and a water-chiller system to remove heat.

Cold_Deck.label: Cold Deck
Cold_Deck.description: Part of a dual duct air handling unit that supplies cooling to a building

Cooling_Discharge_Air_Temperature_Deadba.label: Cooling Discharge Air Temperature Deadband Setpoint
Cooling_Discharge_Air_Temperature_Deadba.description: Sets the size of a deadband of temperature of cooling discharge air

Supply_Air_Temperature_Deadband_Setpoint.description: Sets the size of a deadband of temperature of supply air

Discharge_Air_Duct_Pressure_Status.description: Indicates if air pressure in discharge duct is within expected bounds

Discharge_Air_Flow_Demand_Setpoint.description: Sets the rate of discharge air flow required for a process

Air_Flow_Demand_Setpoint.label: Air Flow Demand Setpoint
Air_Flow_Demand_Setpoint.description: Sets the rate of air flow required for a process

Discharge_Air_Flow_High_Reset_Setpoint.label: Discharge Air Flow High Reset Setpoint

Discharge_Air_Flow_Low_Reset_Setpoint.label: Discharge Air Flow Low Reset Setpoint

Discharge_Air_Flow_Sensor.label: Discharge Air Flow Sensor
Discharge_Air_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of discharge air

Discharge_Air_Humidity_Sensor.label: Discharge Air Humidity Sensor
Discharge_Air_Humidity_Sensor.description: Measures the relative humidity of discharge air

Smoke_Alarm.label: Smoke Alarm
Smoke_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with smoke.

Discharge_Air_Static_Pressure_Deadband_S.label: Discharge Air Static Pressure Deadband Setpoint
Discharge_Air_Static_Pressure_Deadband_S.description: Sets the size of a deadband of static pressure of discharge air

Discharge_Air_Static_Pressure_Setpoint.label: Discharge Air Static Pressure Setpoint
Discharge_Air_Static_Pressure_Setpoint.description: Sets static pressure of discharge air

Static_Pressure_Deadband_Setpoint.description: Sets the size of a deadband of static pressure

Supply_Air_Static_Pressure_Setpoint.description: Sets static pressure of supply air

Discharge_Air_Temperature_Alarm.description: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the temperature of discharge air.

Discharge_Air_Temperature_Deadband_Setpo.label: Discharge Air Temperature Deadband Setpoint

Discharge_Air_Temperature_Reset_Differen.label: Discharge Air Temperature Reset Differential Setpoint

Discharge_Air_Temperature_Sensor.description: Measures the temperature of discharge air

Air_Temperature_Setpoint_Limit.label: Air Temperature Setpoint Limit

Effective_Cooling_Zone_Air_Temperature_S.label: Effective Cooling Zone Air Temperature Setpoint
Effective_Cooling_Zone_Air_Temperature_S.description: The effective cooling setpoint for a specific zone in a building.

Effective_Heating_Zone_Air_Temperature_S.label: Effective Heating Zone Air Temperature Setpoint
Effective_Heating_Zone_Air_Temperature_S.description: The effective heating setpoint for a specific zone in a building.

Effective_Target_Zone_Air_Temperature_Se.label: Effective Target Zone Air Temperature Setpoint
Effective_Target_Zone_Air_Temperature_Se.description: Target Setpoint (also known as Common Setpoint) is a reference point representing the desired air temperature in a specific zone of a building. Elevator_Space.label: Elevator Space
Elevator_Space.description: The vertical space in whcih an elevator ascends and descends

Entering_Chilled_Water_Flow_Sensor.label: Entering Chilled Water Flow Sensor
Entering_Chilled_Water_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the rate of flow of chilled entering water

Entering_Chilled_Water_Temperature_Senso.label: Entering Chilled Water Temperature Sensor
Entering_Chilled_Water_Temperature_Senso.description: Measures the temperature of chilled water that is enteringed to a cooling tower

Entering_Chilled_Water_Temperature_Setpo.description: Sets the temperature of entering (downstream of the chilled water load) chilled water

Entering_Condenser_Water_Flow_Sensor.description: Measures the flow of the entering condenser water

Entering_Condenser_Water_Temperature_Sen.label: Entering Condenser Water Temperature Sensor
Entering_Condenser_Water_Temperature_Sen.description: Measures the temperature of the entering condenser water

Entering_Condenser_Water_Temperature_Set.label: Entering Condenser Water Temperature Setpoint

Entering_Medium_Temperature_Hot_Water_Te.description: Measures the temperature of medium-temperature hot water entering a hot water system

Entering_Water_Temperature_Sensor.description: Measures the temperature of entering water

Heating_Discharge_Air_Temperature_Deadba.label: Heating Discharge Air Temperature Deadband Setpoint
